commit.message:
Don't force wide string on possibly `CreateFileA`.

If the library is not compiled with unicode. Then `CreateFile` points to `CreateFileA`. And will be called with a wide string.

commit.message:
Revert "Do not calculate record_info repeatedly"

This reverts commit 5bf3db24fa2c6fc49765cc325d16a60e9ad921dd.

This commit introduced an unintended ABI change. Users of this library
allocate the space for MMDB_s. Any increase in size of MMDB_s may cause
us to write off the end of the struct unless the caller is recompiled.
